│ stop({"edit_points": [[7260, 7314,                                                     │
│ "llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/LoopVectorize.cpp"]], "thoughts": "1. Understanding the │
│ Issue:\nThe crash is an assertion failure in LoopVectorizationPlanner::computeBestVF:  │
│ the VPlan cost-model selected a different VF than the legacy cost-model, and the guard │
│ meant to allow disagreement when the VPlan contains additional simplifications did not │
│ detect any. Assertions in this area assume that if the VPlan and legacy models         │
│ disagree, the VPlan must have extra simplifications not modeled by the legacy cost. If │
│ this detection misses a valid case of discrepancy, we abort.\n\n2. Analyzing opt's     │
│ Log:\nScalarEvolution reports suspicious results for the loop, e.g., constant max      │
│ backedge-taken count is i64 -2 and backedge-taken count as (2 + (-1 *                  │
│ %spec.select))<nsw>. While this points to questionable SCEV reasoning for this loop    │
│ shape, the immediate crash is due to the assertion that fails because BestFactor.Width │
│ != LegacyVF.Width and planContainsAdditionalSimplifications returns false. From the    │
│ code, we also see that precomputeCosts explicitly excludes the backedge terminator     │
│ from branch cost computation to avoid mismatches in the number of replicate regions vs │
│ branches.\n\n3. Root Cause Analysis:\nThe guard function                               │
│ planContainsAdditionalSimplifications is intended to detect whether the VPlan includes │
│ simplifications that the legacy cost model didn’t account for. However, the            │
│ cost-precomputation logic intentionally skips the cost of the loop latch terminator    │
│ (the backedge) because the number of replicate regions in VPlan may not match the      │
│ number of branches. The legacy cost model (used by selectVectorizationFactor via       │
│ CM.expectedCost) can include branch costs that the VPlan precomputation does not,      │
│ causing a legitimate cost discrepancy. Since planContainsAdditionalSimplifications     │
│ only skips PHIs in the header and doesn't treat the latch terminator specially, it     │
│ fails to recognize this intended exclusion as a \"simplification\" and thus returns    │
│ false, causing the assertion to trigger even though the discrepancy is expected.\n\n4. │
│ Proposed Edit Point(s)\nEdit file:                                                     │
